[{"id":"VR914709","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two diagrams that are labeled “Setup, Side View” and “Viewing Screen, Front View.” The Setup, Side View diagram shows a laser, a plate, and a screen on a horizontal surface. The laser is on the left, the plate with two narrow openings is in the middle, and the viewing screen is on the right. The horizontal distance between the plate and the viewing screen is labeled L. The laser directs a laser beam horizontally to the right through the plate. The laser beam continues to move horizontally to the right and ends on the viewing screen. The Viewing Screen, Front View diagram shows the pattern formed by the laser beam on the viewing screen. The background of the viewing screen is black. The pattern is comprised of seven equal-size white rectangles that are evenly spaced from each other. An arrow pointing to the fourth rectangle indicates Central Bright Fringe. An arrow pointing to the sixth rectangle indicates Second Bright Fringe. The horizontal distance from Central Bright Fringe to the Second Bright Fringe is labeled “?”.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR914709.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The figure shows a setup where light of wavelength <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lambda\"><math alttext=\"lambda\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>λ</mi></math></span></span> from a laser is incident on a plate with two narrow openings. Each opening has a width <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"w\"><math alttext=\"w\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>w</mi></math></span></span>, and the centers of the openings are separated by a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"s\"><math alttext=\"s\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>s</mi></math></span></span>. The light forms an interference pattern on a viewing screen that is a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"L\"><math alttext=\"L\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>L</mi></math></span></span> away from the plate, as shown. What is the approximate distance – indicated in the figure by the question mark − between the centers of the central bright fringe and the second bright fringe away from the central fringe? Assume that small-angle approximations are valid for the fringes shown in the interference pattern.</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR914709_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator lambda L, and denominator s, end fraction\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator lambda L, and denominator s, end fraction\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>λ</mi><mi>L</mi></mrow><mi>s</mi></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator lambda L, and denominator w, end fraction\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator lambda L, and denominator w, end fraction\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>λ</mi><mi>L</mi></mrow><mi>w</mi></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator 2 lambda L, and denominator s, end fraction\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator 2 lambda L, and denominator s, end fraction\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>λ</mi><mi>L</mi></mrow><mi>s</mi></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator 2 lambda L, and denominator w, end fraction\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator 2 lambda L, and denominator w, end fraction\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>λ</mi><mi>L</mi></mrow><mi>w</mi></mfrac></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":2}]